{\r\n    private static class Foo\r\n    {\r\n        String value;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    @Test\r\n    public void testPercentage() throws Exception\r\n    {\r\n        Foo foo1 = new Foo();\r\n        foo1.value = \"foo\";\r\n\r\n        Foo foo2 = new Foo();\r\n        foo2.value = \"%foo\";\r\n\r\n        assertThat(foo1).isEqualToComparingFieldByFieldRecursively(foo2);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is the exception with stacktrace:\r\n```\r\njava.util.MissingFormatArgumentException: Format specifier '%f'\r\n\tat java.util.Formatter.format(Formatter.java:2519)\r\n\tat java.util.Formatter.format(Formatter.java:2455)\r\n\tat java.lang.String.format(String.java:2940)\r\n\tat org.assertj.core.util.Strings.formatIfArgs(Strings.java:92)\r\n\tat org.assertj.core.error.MessageFormatter.format(MessageFormatter.java:61)\r\n\tat org.assertj.core.error.BasicErrorMessageFactory.create(BasicErrorMessageFactory.java:110)\r\n\tat org.assertj.core.internal.Failures.failure(Failures.java:116)\r\n\tat org.assertj.core.internal.Objects.assertIsEqualToComparingFieldByFieldRecursively(Objects.java:713)\r\n\tat org.assertj.core.api.AbstractObjectAssert.isEqualToComparingFieldByFieldRecursively(AbstractObjectAssert.java:647)\r\n\tat PercentageTest.testPercentage(PercentageTest.java:26)\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Java 8 specific ?\r\n\r\nI have tested this with AssertJ versions 2.6.0 and 3.8.0.\r\n","closed_by":{"login":"joel-costigliola","id":382613,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM4MjYxMw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/382613?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola","html_url":"https://github.com/joel-costigliola","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscrip